  "texts": [
    "For example, a general form of goal-directed activity is locomotion: purposive movement towards biologically salient targets (food, shelter, nurturing conspecifics) and away from salient threats (predators, aversive environments).",
    "Cognition-relevant norms constrain the means by which these locomotive ends are pursued.",
    "Movement must be guided towards an end with a degree of non-lucky flexibility and responsiveness to other ends that the agent has.",
    "This means, for example, that purely reflexive responses to stimuli aren't enough.",
    "Cognition involves integrating multiple streams of information, facilitating orderly whole-animal responses to the environment (or some relevant swathe of it) considered as a complex unity."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}